-first= Wayne|editor1-last= Somers |title= Encyclopedia of Union College History |year= 2003 |publisher= Union College |location= Schenectady, New York |isbn= 0-912756-31-4}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Tewksbury | first = Donald G. | year = 1932 | title = The Founding of American Colleges and Universities Before the Civil War | publisher = Teachers College, [[Columbia University]]  | location = New York |oclc= 76620}}\n* {{Cite book |title= Joseph Jacques Ram\u00e9e: Architect of Union College |last= Tunnard |first= Christopher |authorlink=Christopher Tunnard |year= 1964 |publisher= Union College |location= Schenectady, New York |oclc= 5291278}}\n* {{Cite book |title= Campus: An American Planning Tradition |last= Turner |first= Paul V. |year= 1984 |publisher= [[MIT Press]] |location= [[Cambridge, Massachusetts]] |isbn= 0-262-20047-3}}\n* {{Cite book |title= Joseph Ram\u00e9e: International Architect of the Revolutionary Era |last= Turner |first= Paul V. |year= 1996 |publisher= [[Cambridge University Press]] |location= [[Cambridge]] |isbn= 0-521-49552-0}}\n* {{Cite book |title=Mr. Jefferson's University |last=Wills |first=Garry |authorlink=Garry Wills |year=2002 |publisher=[[National Geographic Society]] |location=[[Washington, D.C.]] |oclc=97814677 |isbn=0-7922-6531-9 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/mrjeffersonsuniv00garr }}\n* {{Cite book|title=Schenectady County, New York: Its History to the Close of the Nineteenth Century |last=Yates |first=Austin A. |year=1902 |publisher=New York History Company |location=New York |oclc=18738526|isbn=1-153-14534-0}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite book |title= Historical Sketch of Union College |last= Hough |first= Franklin B. |year= 1876 |publisher= Government Printing Office |location= Washington, D.C. |url=https://archive.org/details/historicalsketc00educgoog |oclc= 61597023}}{{via|GB}}\n* {{Cite book |title= Thirty Years in the Life of a College |last= Huntley |first= C. William |year= 1985 |publish