{"title_page": "Claude Lafortune", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian artist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Claude Lafortune\n| image         = Claude Lafortune - 04 (cropped).JPG\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Lafortune in 2012\n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = 5 July 1936\n| birth_place   = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|df=y|2020|04|19|1936|07|05}}\n| death_place   = [[Longueuil]], Quebec, Canada\n| nationality   = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Artist\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Claude Lafortune''' (5 July 1936 \u2013 19 April 2020) was a Canadian [[paper art]]ist, set decorator and TV personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.journaldemontreal.com/2020/04/19/lanimateur-claude-lafortune-decede-des-suites-de-la-covid-19|title=L'animateur Claude Lafortune d\u00e9c\u00e8de des suites de la COVID-19|date=19 April 2020|work=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|language=French}}</ref>\n==Biography==\n\nA graduate of the [[\u00c9cole des beaux-arts de Montr\u00e9al]], Lafortune collaborated on many graphic design projects before he became famous for his paper art.\n\nHe had an exhibit devoted to his paper art work\u2014titled ''Colle, papier, ciseaux''\u2014at the Mus\u00e9e des cultures du monde in [[Nicolet, Quebec]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musees.qc.ca/fr/professionnel/produits-services/expos-itinerantes/colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Colle, papier, ciseaux|work=Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 des Mus\u00e9es du Qu\u00e9bec|language=French|url-status=dead|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20190514040439/https://www.musees.qc.ca/fr/professionnel/produits-services/expos-itinerantes/colle-papier-ciseaux|archivedate=14 May 2019}}</ref> The exhibition has traveled to [[Longueuil]], [[Montreal]], [[Terrebonne, Quebec|Terrebonne]], [[Salaberry-de-Valleyfield]], [[Lachine, Quebec|Lachine]], [[Chicoutimi]], [[Bonaventure, Quebec|Bonaventure]], [[La Malbaie]] and [[New Brunswick]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museedesreligions.qc.ca/nos-expositions/passees/colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Colle, Papier, Ciseaux|work=Mus\u00e9e des Religions du Monde|language=French}}</ref>\n\nLaFortune died in [[Longueuil]], Quebec, aged 83, after contracting the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] virus during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Quebec]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journaldemontreal.com/2020/04/19/lanimateur-claude-lafortune-decede-des-suites-de-la-covid-19|title=L'animateur Claude Lafortune d\u00e9c\u00e8de des suites de la COVID-19|last=Scali|first=Dominique|website=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|access-date=20 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Prizes==\n*Prix du meilleur d\u00e9cor at the Festival d'Art Dramatique de Montr\u00e9al (1965)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coffreauxsouvenirs.starquebec.net/L/lafortune_claude.htm|title=Claude Lafortune|work=Le coffre aux souvenirs|language=French|url-status=dead|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160303231818/http://coffreauxsouvenirs.starquebec.net/L/lafortune_claude.htm|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n*Prix Alvine-B\u00e9lisle (1977-1978)\n*Prix de litt\u00e9rature de jeunesse of the [[Canada Council]] (1977)\n*Prix Anik of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] (1978)\n*The International Association of Printing House Craftsmen Prize (1982)\n*Prize of the Association Nationale des t\u00e9l\u00e9spectateurs (1982)\n*Prix de reconnaissance de l'Office des communications sociales pour l'ensemble de l'\u0153uvre d'une personne \u00e0 la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision religieuse (1988)\n*Prix d'excellence de l'Alliance pour l'enfant et la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision (1992)\n*Prix G\u00e9meaux of the [[Academy of Canadian Cinema & Television]] (1994)\n*Prix sp\u00e9cial de l'Alliance pour l'enfant et la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision pour le couronnement d'une carri\u00e8re (1995)\n*Prix Paul-Blouin of  [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] (2000)\n*''Troph\u00e9e le Masque, La tr\u00e8s belle histoire de No\u00ebl'' (2002)\n*Prix Citoyen d'exception of the City of Longueuil (2016)\n*''Docteur honoris causa'' from the [[Universit\u00e9 du Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lelezard.com/communique-18757532.html|title=L'artiste visuel Claude Lafortune recevra un doctorat honoris causa de l'UQAM|date=13 May 2019|work=Le L\u00e9zard|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ici.radio-canada.ca/premiere/emissions/medium-large/segments/entrevue/117714/claude-lafortune-evangile-papier-colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Claude Lafortune, le magicien du papier|date=13 May 2019|work=Radio-Canada|language=French}}</ref>\n*Gold Medal of the Lieutenant-Governor of Quebec (2018)\n\n==Television appearances==\n*''La Ribouldingue'' (1968\u20131971)\n*''[[Sol et Gobelet]]'' (1968\u20131971)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lafabriqueculturelle.tv/capsules/10853/une-vie-de-papier-l-etonnant-parcours-de-claude-lafortune|title=Une vie de papier|date=28 March 2018|work=LaFabriqueCulturelle.tv|language=French}}</ref>\n*''Du soleil \u00e0 cinq cents'' (1973\u20131976)\n*''L'\u00c9vangile en papier'' (1975\u20131976)\n*''La Bible en papier'' (1976\u20131977)\n*''Es-tu d'accord?'' (1976\u20131977)\n*''L'\u00c9glise en papier'' (1977\u20131978)\n*''Qu\u00e9b\u00e9kio'' (since 1980)\n*''La souris verte''\n*''Nicole et Pierre'' (1986\u20131988)\n*''Parcelles de soleil'' (1988\u20132000)\n\n==Film appearances==\n''IXE-13''\n==Stage theater appearances==\n*''Na\u00efves Hirondelles'' (1965)\n*''Ballade pour un R\u00e9volutionnaire'' (1965)\n*''La grosse t\u00eate'' (1969)\n*''La tr\u00e8s belle histoire de No\u00ebl'' (2001\u20132006)\n*''Don Quichotte'' (2009)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb name|id=0481020}}\n* {{Discogs artist|Claude Lafortune}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lafortune, Claude}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Paper art]]\n[[Category:Canadian male artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian sculptors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian sculptors]]\n[[Category:Male sculptors]]\n[[Category:Canadian television hosts]]\n[[Category:Canadian set decorators]]\n[[Category:People from Longueuil]]\n[[Category:People from Longueuil (agglomeration)]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian artist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Claude Lafortune\n| image         = Claude Lafortune - 04 (cropped).JPG\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Lafortune in 2012\n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = 5 July 1936\n| birth_place   = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|df=y|2020|04|19|1936|07|05}}\n| death_place   = [[Longueuil]], Quebec, Canada\n| nationality   = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Artist\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Claude Lafortune''' (5 July 1936 \u2013 19 April 2020) was a Canadian [[paper art]]ist, set decorator and TV personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.journaldemontreal.com/2020/04/19/lanimateur-claude-lafortune-decede-des-suites-de-la-covid-19|title=L'animateur Claude Lafortune d\u00e9c\u00e8de des suites de la COVID-19|date=19 April 2020|work=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|language=French}}</ref>\n==Biography==\n\nA graduate of the [[\u00c9cole des beaux-arts de Montr\u00e9al]], Lafortune collaborated on many graphic design projects before he became famous for his paper art.\n\nHe had an exhibit devoted to his paper art work\u2014titled ''Colle, papier, ciseaux''\u2014at the Mus\u00e9e des cultures du monde in [[Nicolet, Quebec]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musees.qc.ca/fr/professionnel/produits-services/expos-itinerantes/colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Colle, papier, ciseaux|work=Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 des Mus\u00e9es du Qu\u00e9bec|language=French|url-status=dead|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20190514040439/https://www.musees.qc.ca/fr/professionnel/produits-services/expos-itinerantes/colle-papier-ciseaux|archivedate=14 May 2019}}</ref> The exhibition has traveled to [[Longueuil]], [[Montreal]], [[Terrebonne, Quebec|Terrebonne]], [[Salaberry-de-Valleyfield]], [[Lachine, Quebec|Lachine]], [[Chicoutimi]], [[Bonaventure, Quebec|Bonaventure]], [[La Malbaie]] and [[New Brunswick]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.museedesreligions.qc.ca/nos-expositions/passees/colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Colle, Papier, Ciseaux|work=Mus\u00e9e des Religions du Monde|language=French}}</ref>\n\nLaFortune died in [[Longueuil]], Quebec, aged 83, after contracting the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] virus during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Quebec]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journaldemontreal.com/2020/04/19/lanimateur-claude-lafortune-decede-des-suites-de-la-covid-19|title=L'animateur Claude Lafortune d\u00e9c\u00e8de des suites de la COVID-19|last=Scali|first=Dominique|website=Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al|access-date=20 April 2020|language=fr}}</ref>\n\n==Prizes==\n*Prix du meilleur d\u00e9cor at the Festival d'Art Dramatique de Montr\u00e9al (1965)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coffreauxsouvenirs.starquebec.net/L/lafortune_claude.htm|title=Claude Lafortune|work=Le coffre aux souvenirs|language=French|url-status=dead|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20160303231818/http://coffreauxsouvenirs.starquebec.net/L/lafortune_claude.htm|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n*Prix Alvine-B\u00e9lisle (1977-1978)\n*Prix de litt\u00e9rature de jeunesse of the [[Canada Council]] (1977)\n*Prix Anik of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] (1978)\n*The International Association of Printing House Craftsmen Prize (1982)\n*Prize of the Association Nationale des t\u00e9l\u00e9spectateurs (1982)\n*Prix de reconnaissance de l'Office des communications sociales pour l'ensemble de l'\u0153uvre d'une personne \u00e0 la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision religieuse (1988)\n*Prix d'excellence de l'Alliance pour l'enfant et la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision (1992)\n*Prix G\u00e9meaux of the [[Academy of Canadian Cinema & Television]] (1994)\n*Prix sp\u00e9cial de l'Alliance pour l'enfant et la t\u00e9l\u00e9vision pour le couronnement d'une carri\u00e8re (1995)\n*Prix Paul-Blouin of  [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] (2000)\n*''Troph\u00e9e le Masque, La tr\u00e8s belle histoire de No\u00ebl'' (2002)\n*Prix Citoyen d'exception of the City of Longueuil (2016)\n*''Docteur honoris causa'' from the [[Universit\u00e9 du Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lelezard.com/communique-18757532.html|title=L'artiste visuel Claude Lafortune recevra un doctorat honoris causa de l'UQAM|date=13 May 2019|work=Le L\u00e9zard|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ici.radio-canada.ca/premiere/emissions/medium-large/segments/entrevue/117714/claude-lafortune-evangile-papier-colle-papier-ciseaux|title=Claude Lafortune, le magicien du papier|date=13 May 2019|work=Radio-Canada|language=French}}</ref>\n*Gold Medal of the Lieutenant-Governor of Quebec (2018)\n\n==Television appearances==\n*''La Ribouldingue'' (1968\u20131971)\n*''[[Sol et Gobelet]]'' (1968\u20131971)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lafabriqueculturelle.tv/capsules/10853/une-vie-de-papier-l-etonnant-parcours-de-claude-lafortune|title=Une vie de papier|date=28 March 2018|work=LaFabriqueCulturelle.tv|language=French}}</ref>\n*''Du soleil \u00e0 cinq cents'' (1973\u20131976)\n*''L'\u00c9vangile en papier'' (1975\u20131976)\n*''La Bible en papier'' (1976\u20131977)\n*''Es-tu d'accord?'' (1976\u20131977)\n*''L'\u00c9glise en papier'' (1977\u20131978)\n*''Qu\u00e9b\u00e9kio'' (since 1980)\n*''La souris verte''\n*''Nicole et Pierre'' (1986\u20131988)\n*''Parcelles de soleil'' (1988\u20132000)\n\n==Film appearances==\n''IXE-13''\n==Stage theater appearances==\n*''Na\u00efves Hirondelles'' (1965)\n*''Ballade pour un R\u00e9volutionnaire'' (1965)\n*''La grosse t\u00eate'' (1969)\n*''La tr\u00e8s belle histoire de No\u00ebl'' (2001\u20132006)\n*''Don Quichotte'' (2009)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n*{{imdb name|id=0481020}}\n* {{Discogs artist|Claude Lafortune}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lafortune, Claude}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Paper art]]\n[[Category:Canadian male artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian sculptors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian sculptors]]\n[[Category:Male sculptors]]\n[[Category:Canadian television hosts]]\n[[Category:Canadian set decorators]]\n[[Category:People from Longueuil]]\n[[Category:People from Longueuil (agglomeration)]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada]]\n", "name_user": "All Hallow's Wraith", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal Links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Claude_Lafortune"}
